e cut. Fine for the documented ASCII-leaning scope. **Fix if ever wired to live Unicode:** `const chars = Array.from(text); ...chars.slice(0, Math.max(0, max - ellipsis.length)).join('') + ellipsis;` or `Intl.Segmenter`.\n- **`src/lib/slug.ts:12` — `slugify` is ASCII-only by design** (`Café déjà vu → caf-d-j-vu`, per the docstring). Correct and intentional. **Backlog note:** add `text.normalize('NFKD')` + combining-mark strip before `[^a-z0-9]+` only if SEO needs `café → cafe`. Product call, not a defect.\n\n### Scope note\nPure internal utilities, **zero call sites** — no rendered-UI or external-contract change. Tests pin the documented edge cases (empty/all-separator slug → `\"\"`, idempotent slug, ASCII reduction; clamp bounds + NaN/RangeError; FP-safe `roundTo(1.005,2)`; ellipsis-against-budget; whitespace-preserving titleCase). These files are **untracked at base `8f2a019`** — not yet committed; this review covers the on-disk content. ADR-0001 findings (cr-f1..f4) live in `format.ts`/`KeywordTable.tsx` — untouched here — so none are re-flagged.\n\n> **On the Dev Clone's drift report:** confirmed accurate at the time and still partly so — HEAD is `8f2a019`, README has no 0.2.x line, the payload commits `c868c48`/`28d0889` don't exist on this tree. The one change since: the ADR-0002 utils have re-materialized as untracked files (they were absent when the Dev Clone ran).\n\n---\n**Verdict: APPROVE** — no security or correctness issues; suite green and typecheck clean, both verified independently. The two low notes are forward-looking quality items for live-Unicode wiring, not merge blockers. Consistent with the human-approved longitudinal policy on these modules.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

