{"user_message": {"title": "Code Review — APPROVE (ADR-0002 parallel utils, branch dev-clone/adr-0002-parallel-utils @ f52b780)", "content": "## Verdict: APPROVE (with notes)\n\nReviewed the three ADR-0002 pure-utility modules against the live tree. The handoff's commit hash matched git this run (`f52b780`, clean tree) — the previously-uncommitted work is now committed on the dev-clone branch. **No critical, security, or correctness defects.** Two low-severity, forward-looking quality notes — neither gates the merge.\n\n### Independent verification (not trusting the handoff)\n| Check | Result |\n|---|---|\n| Branch / commit | ✅ `dev-clone/adr-0002-parallel-utils` @ `f52b780`, tree clean |\n| Changeset scope vs `main` | ✅ ADR-0002 only — `slug.ts`/`num.ts`/`str.ts` + their tests, `package.json`, ADR doc |\n| `tsc --noEmit` | ✅ exit 0 |\n| `npm test` | ✅ **24 pass / 0 fail** (~202ms, re-run locally) |\n| Cross-imports between modules | ✅ **none** — all three import-free, file-disjoint, parallel-safe |\n| External call sites in `src/` | ✅ none (lone `truncate` hit is a Tailwind class in `MapPackCard.tsx:36`) |\n\n```chart\nTests passing: 24\nTests failing: 0\nSuite runtime ms: 202\n```\n\n### 🔴 Critical / 🟠 High / Security\n_None._ All three modules are pure functions over primitive inputs — no injection, auth, I/O, or data-leak surface. `num.ts` is explicitly finite-safe: `clamp` (`src/lib/num.ts:13`) throws `RangeError` on non-finite/inverted bounds and propagates `NaN` rather than hiding it; `roundTo` (`src/lib/num.ts:34`) returns non-finite input unchanged and floor-guards `decimals`. Notably **better hygiene than the latent `format.ts` NaN gaps** tracked under ADR-0001 — the team carried that lesson forward.\n\n### 🟢 Low (quality — non-gating, forward-looking)\n- **`src/lib/str.ts:12-15` — `truncate` splits on UTF-16 code units.** `text.length`/`text.slice` can sever a surrogate pair or combining sequence (emoji, accented grapheme) at the cut, yielding a broken glyph before the ellipsis. Fine for the documented ASCII-leaning presentation scope. **Fix if ever wired to live Unicode** (business names, titles): `const chars = Array.from(text); if (chars.length <= max) return text; return chars.slice(0, Math.max(0, max - ellipsis.length)).join('') + ellipsis;` or `Intl.Segmenter` for grapheme safety.\n- **`src/lib/slug.ts:12` — `slugify` is ASCII-only by design** (`Café déjà vu → caf-d-j-vu`, per the docstring). Correct and intentional, not a defect. **Backlog note:** add `text.normalize('NFKD')` + combining-mark strip before the `[^a-z0-9]+` replace only if SEO needs diacritic transliteration (`café → cafe`). Product call, not a defect.\n\n### Scope note\nPure internal utilities, **zero call sites** — no rendered-UI or external-contract change, no sign-off gate. Tests pin the documented edge cases (empty/all-separator slug → `\"\"`, idempotent slug, ASCII reduction; clamp bounds + NaN/RangeError; FP-safe `roundTo(1.005,2)`; ellipsis-against-budget; whitespace-preserving titleCase). ADR-0001 findings (cr-f1..f4) live in `format.ts`/`KeywordTable.tsx` — **untouched by this changeset** — so none are re-flagged here.\n\n---\n**Verdict: APPROVE** — no security or correctness issues; suite green and typecheck clean, both verified independently against `f52b780`. Consistent with the human-approved longitudinal policy on these modules. The two low notes are forward-looking quality items for live-Unicode wiring, not merge blockers. Safe to ship.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

